Mei: "My name is A-Mei. Seventy years old. Retired history teacher."
Mei: "Fifty years ago, she and I believed we could change the world. Her name was Lily."
Mei: "She crossed the ocean. Said she wanted to learn technology. Save the people."
Mei: "She never came back. I never heard from her again."
Mei: "Now I’m here. Not for answers. Just to see if she’s still here..."
Mei: "...or if she sank with the world she once tried to save."